oai_dc:dc.dc:title: ENGINEERING PROPERTIES OF SEA FLOOR SEDIMENTS FROM LA JOLLA CANYON
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Noorany, Iraj
Zinser, Robert A.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: La Jolla Canyon
sea bed
bed sediment
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Near surface sea floor sediments were obtained "by the tracked underwater -vehicle RUM from four locations on the floor of the La Jolla Canyon. The sediments were clayey silts of high plasticity. The engineering properties of the sediments, including grain size, index properties, strength and compressibility, were determined.
